						<summary>

						<p>Left niche in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the Mahādēva temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record states that Rēvaseṭṭi and Jinnaṇa, sons of Basaviseṭṭi and his wife Lokkaṇabbe and disciple of Muni-Suvrata-Siddhāntadēva got the image of goddess Padmāvati made.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
